%% Diagram: useFetch race-condition cancellation with AbortController
%% Type: sequence
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant C as Component
    participant E as useEffect
    participant N as Network

    U->>C: typed userId = 1
    C->>E: setup(userId=1)
    E->>N: fetch("/users/1", signal=abort#1)

    U->>C: typed userId = 2 (before /users/1 resolves)
    C->>E: cleanup for userId=1
    E->>N: abort#1.abort()
    N-->>E: rejects with AbortError (filtered)
    C->>E: setup(userId=2)
    E->>N: fetch("/users/2", signal=abort#2)
    N-->>E: 200 OK { user: 2 }
    E->>C: dispatch({ type: 'success', data })

    Note over E,N: Without abort, /users/1 could resolve<br/>after /users/2 and overwrite the<br/>visible state ("last write wins" bug).
